Package frogger.controllers

Class GameController

java.lang.Object
frogger.controllers.GameController
public class GameController
extends Object

The class GameController manages the core flow of the Frogger game.

Methods in GameController called to pass values, save values, call methods as a mediator between SceneController, StartSceneController, InfoSceneController, EndSceneController, HSSceneController.

GameController used to detect Level child class completions to facilitate automatic level swap through calling SceneController.changeScene(Integer).

Core controller for Frogger game MVC design pattern and Mediator between SceneController, StartSceneController, InfoSceneController, EndSceneController, HSSceneController in Mediator design pattern.

Initialized as a Singleton to avoid multiple instances as it may cause errors.

      public void setSceneControllers​(javafx.scene.Scene scene, SceneController sceneController, EndSceneController endSceneController, HSSceneController hsSceneController)

      Set the Scene, SceneController objects that will be called and used by GameController.

      Parameters:
      scene - the instance of Scene used for display.
      sceneController - the instance of SceneController to be called when switching scenes.
      endSceneController - the instance of EndSceneController to be called to generate EndScene when all Level are completed.
      hsSceneController - the instance of HSSceneController to be called to generate HighScoreScene.
